    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Institutions having facilities where people are legally committed as punishment for a crime or while awaiting trial. In North America, the term specifically denotes a facility run by the state or federal government for those who have been convicted of serious crimes, in contrast to a locally run facility for those awaiting trial or convicted of minor offences. Use "jails (institutions)" for facilities for offenders sentenced either for lesser crimes or relatively short terms.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000039651/Canadian Thesaurus of Construction Science and Technology (1978)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instellingen met faciliteiten waar mensen op wettelijke basis vastzitten als straf voor een misdrijf of in afwachting van berechting. In Noord-Amerika verwijst de term 'prisons' specifiek naar een door de staat of federale regering gerunde faciliteit voor mensen die van ernstige misdrijven zijn beschuldigd, in tegenstelling tot lokaal bestuurde faciliteiten voor mensen in afwachting van berechting of voor kleinere misdrijven. Gebruik 'huizen van bewaring (instellingen)' voor misdadigers die voor kleinere misdrijven gestraft worden of een relatief korte straf hebben gekregen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instituições com instalações onde as pessoas são legalmente cometidas como punição por um crime ou enquanto aguardam julgamento. Na América do Norte, o termo indica especificamente uma instalação administrada pelo governo estadual ou federal para aqueles que foram condenados por crimes graves, em contraste com uma instalação administrada localmente para aqueles que aguardam julgamento ou condenados por delitos menores. Use "prisões (instituições)" para instalações para criminosos condenados por crimes menores ou por períodos relativamente curtos. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具有專門設施，可供合法收容受刑人或等待判決者的機構。此詞彙在北美特指由州政府或聯邦政府管轄、專門收容重罪犯的機構，和地方政府所管轄之拘留輕罪犯或等待判決者的機構有所區隔。若指稱收容輕罪犯或刑期較短之受刑人的機構，使用「拘留所(機構)」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
